While the graphics are lackluster I can easily overlooked them by the fact that everything about it seems realistic from the F 111s ejection system and its Nook of the earth auto pilot system to the F5's heat seeking missile that you have to manually lock onto the target and it's surreal fighter gameplay and the satisfaction of watching a missile actually be able to take a target in one hit and you know you aren't using an overpowered weapon because they have it to and it feels genuine using the radar to locate the enemy then switching from SCAN mode to BORE mode to lock on then get within range and wait for the audio que to launch that beutefull AIM 9 and send that NVAF fighter to gulag also the community is great with people dedicating their time to become ATC and keep the busy servers airports running smoothly

Love the series. Worth the $. My issues. Really needs custom location controls. Current placement is to close on phones and not easy to use more than one control at a time on tablets. Missions rapidly become monotonous. Almost no air AI. Falling into the ground on take off happens a lot. No countermeasures? Sams can be avoided but mig launched missiles mean restarting most of the time. Working cockpit is awesome but fairly useless on phones. Speed and alt num needed. Choosing plane and load out then getting random mission gets old. Show mission then pick aircraft sorely needed. ESPECIALLY if you pick a helicopter. Missions to far away. It's a sim. I get it but can get old. Some missions time out before reaching area. Not enough enemy air assets. No auto center in ext cam. Controls are cramped. Rudder needs to be mid rgt screen and weapon fire and select moved apart. Reload/change load menu needed. Landing at base for reload is a crap shoot. Quick mission builder needed. Still very worth the price just needs a bit more tweaking to be awesome. It's a good game but the deficiencies mount the more you play.
